sub_title: Veterinary student I Farm Animal Vet I Aquaculture Research I Salomon I Animal Nutrition I Vet surgeon I International I Sports and Outdoor I Doctorand I looking forward to work in North America
summary:
Through my veterinary education at three european universities, as well as various internships and side jobs around the globe, I was able to prepare myself for a career in an international environment.
I am very motivated to work together with various people and make use of my international network with the help of my multilanguage communication skills. 
Additionally, I believe that I can make a valuable asset to any highly driven team, through my business and service orientated mindset as well as my leadership and teawork skills which were aquired through
the training as an army officer and my passion for team sports. 
I am always on the lookout for new challenges in the wide field of veterinary medicine and 
grew particularly intrested in the field of aquaculture nutrition.  Therefore my master thesis was based on RAS aquaculture and plant based fish diets. Currently I am enhancing my knowledge in this field by doing a doctorate on salmon nutrion, while working as a mixed animal vet and in the fish unit of the Swedish districveterinarians.
